• ond all as much as is possible, for men to be possest of, being made an imitator according to th • power of Christ who is God. He that can find in these words an Apostolical Spirit breathing, hath little acquaintance with the Apostolical writings. How unlike is this to that of the Apostle 1 Cor. 3.5. Who then is Paul, and who Apollo, but Ministers by whom ye believe?

