que ipso rei usu & exequutione firmata, ut nimirum, possent Chorepiscopi etiam Presbyteros & Diaconos ordinare, permittente, licet non simul ordinante Episcopo loci. But how will it be proved▪ may some say, That these Chorepiscopi were onely Presbyters and not Bishops? For if this can be clearly made out, it will undeniably follow, That according to the judgment of Antiquity, Presbyters had not onely the inward power, but also the outward exercise of Ordination for a long space. Now that these Chorepiscopi were meer Presbyters, appeares;
